article.description: — Nicolas Timberlake's 23 points helped Towson defeat Penn 80-74 on Sunday night.
article.headline: Timberlake's 23 help Towson knock off Pennsylvania 80-74
article.linkText: Timberlake's 23 help Towson knock off Pennsylvania 80-74
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — Nicolas Timberlake's 23 points helped Towson defeat Penn 80-74 on Sunday night. Timberlake added five rebounds for the Tigers (3-0). Cameron Holden scored 17 points and added three steals. Charles Thompson recorded 14 points and shot 4 of 9 from the field and 6 for 8 from the line. Jordan Dingle led the Quakers (0-3) in scoring, finishing with 24 points and three steals. Clark Slajchert added 21 points for Pennsylvania. In addition, Nick Spinoso had 12 points, four assists and two blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
